         <abstract>
            <p>Among small-capitalization firms, defined as those having market values below $2 billion, some are consistent free cash flow generators, have low financial leverage, and sell at low free cash flow multiples. Presented herein is an investment strategy that selects such securities into a "long" portfolio with returns that outperform the market index, returns of similar-sized securities, returns of firms with similar book-to-market-value ratios, and returns of similar-risk (beta) securities.</p>
          </abstract>
